I"<p>Do this after installing Xorg but before installing a DE. The next time I install Arch I’ll actually blog about it properly but this is something that might be useful real quick. Also, if you’re trying to install Bumblebee on any other flavor,</p>

<p>don’t.</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>sudo pacman -S bumblebee mesa xf86-video-intel lib32-virtualgl lib32-nvidia-utils
sudo gpasswd -a $USER bumblebee
sudo systemctl enable bumblebee
</code></pre></div></div>
